org.json.stream

Class JSONLimitBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.json.stream.JSONLimitBuilder

  • public final class JSONLimitBuilder
extends java.lang.Object
    Builds a JSON object model using events supplied from JSONLimitStreamReader, using secure principles derived from XML parsers.

    This class is similar in its external contract to the JSONObjectBuilder class, but intended to be more robust against untrusted JSON sources. For instance, by not using runtime stack for parsing nested JSON structures, it is less susceptible to stack smashing attempts.

    For some practical limits for parsing JSON data, see BuilderLimits.secureDefaults().

      • buildObjectSubTree

        public static JSONObject buildObjectSubTree(JSONLimitStreamReader reader,
                                            BuilderLimits limits)
                                     throws JSONException
        If the given JSONLimitStreamReader's ParseState was JSONStreamReader.ParseState.OBJECT, return the entire subtree as a JSONObject value. This method advances the parser onto the JSONStreamReader.ParseState.END_OBJECT state.

        If the JSON stream is not parseable as an object, a JSONException will be thrown.

        Parameters:
        reader - A source stream reader.
        limits - the limits imposed on the builder
        Returns:
        a JSONObject representing the subtree starting at the current OBJECT state
        Throws:
        JSONException

      • buildObjectSubTree

        public static <OR> OR buildObjectSubTree(JSONLimitStreamReader reader,
                                         BuilderLimits limits,
                                         StructureCollector<?,?,OR,?> collector)
                                  throws JSONException
        If the given JSONLimitStreamReader's ParseState was JSONStreamReader.ParseState.OBJECT, return the entire subtree as a JSONObject value. This method advances the parser onto the JSONStreamReader.ParseState.END_OBJECT state.

        If the JSON stream is not parseable as an object, a JSONException will be thrown.

        Type Parameters:
        OR - the result type of the JSON object constructed by the factory
        Parameters:
        reader - A source stream reader.
        limits - the limits imposed on the builder
        collector - collector object for creating JSON structures
        Returns:
        a JSONObject representing the subtree starting at the current OBJECT state
        Throws:
        JSONException

      • buildArraySubTree

        public static JSONArray buildArraySubTree(JSONLimitStreamReader reader,
                                          BuilderLimits limits)
                                   throws JSONException
        If the given JSONLimitStreamReader's ParseState was JSONStreamReader.ParseState.ARRAY, return the entire subtree as a JSONArray value. This method advances the parser onto the JSONStreamReader.ParseState.END_ARRAY state.

        If the JSON stream is not parseable as an array, a JSONException will be thrown.

        Parameters:
        reader - A source stream reader.
        limits - the limits imposed on the builder
        Returns:
        a JSONArray representing the subtree starting at the current ARRAY state
        Throws:
        JSONException

                                 throws JSONException
        If the given JSONLimitStreamReader's ParseState was JSONStreamReader.ParseState.ARRAY, return the entire subtree as a JSONArray value. This method advances the parser onto the JSONStreamReader.ParseState.END_ARRAY state.

        If the JSON stream is not parseable as an array, a JSONException will be thrown.

        Type Parameters:
        AR - the result type of the JSON array constructed by the collector
        Parameters:
        reader - A source stream reader.
        limits - the limits imposed on the builder
        collector - collector object for creating JSON structures
        Returns:
        a JSON array representing the subtree starting at the current ARRAY state
        Throws:
        JSONException
